        <div class="disp-col">
          <div class="disp-col-head">Poems</div>
          <div class="disp-col-title">Elegy for a Postbox</div>
          <div class="disp-col-body">They painted it gold for the Games. I preferred it red and slightly wrong.</div>
          <br>
          <div class="disp-col-head">Think Pieces</div>
          <div class="disp-col-title">Against the Considered Opinion</div>
          <div class="disp-col-body">There is a particular arrogance in the person who knows exactly what they think. A short defence of the honest muddle.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
